---
export interface Props {
  showBelowGround?: boolean;
  showAboveGround?: boolean;
  showFormTies?: boolean;
}

const { 
  showBelowGround = true, 
  showAboveGround = true,
  showFormTies = true
} = Astro.props;
---

<div class="nbc-parging-specs bg-orange-50 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center">
    <span class="text-orange-600 mr-2">🧱</span>
    NBC 9.15.6 Parging & Finishing Requirements
  </h3>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-500 p-4 mb-6">
    <p class="text-sm">
      <strong>Purpose:</strong> Parging provides an even, continuous base for dampproofing/waterproofing 
      application and is a critical line of defense for moisture control through foundations.
    </p>
  </div>

  {showBelowGround && (
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-700">9.15.6.1 Foundation Walls Below Ground</h4>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Concrete Block Walls</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>6mm (1/4") minimum thickness</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Even and continuous surface</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Coved over footing junction</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Base for waterproofing</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Application Method</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">1.</span>
              <span>Dampen block surface</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">2.</span>
              <span>Apply scratch coat</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">3.</span>
              <span>Finish coat when tacky</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">4.</span>
              <span>Cure before coating</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  {showAboveGround && (
    <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-700">9.15.6.2 Foundation Walls Above Ground</h4>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Acceptable Finishes</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Tooled mortar joints</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Parging application</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Other suitable finish</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Must prevent rain entry</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Joint Tooling Benefits</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>• Compresses mortar</li>
            <li>• Improves block contact</li>
            <li>• Reduces water penetration</li>
            <li>• Enhances appearance</li>
            <li>• No additional material needed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  {showFormTies && (
    <div class="bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-amber-600">9.15.6.3 Form Ties</h4>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
          <h5 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Removal</h5>
          <ul class="text-xs space-y-1">
            <li>• Cut flush minimum</li>
            <li>• Both wall faces</li>
            <li>• Above & below grade</li>
            <li>• Safety requirement</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
          <h5 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Sealing</h5>
          <ul class="text-xs space-y-1">
            <li>• Fill all holes</li>
            <li>• Use mortar or sealant</li>
            <li>• Smooth surface</li>
            <li>• Waterproof compatible</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
          <h5 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Purpose</h5>
          <ul class="text-xs space-y-1">
            <li>• Substrate prep</li>
            <li>• Water resistance</li>
            <li>• Injury prevention</li>
            <li>• Coating adhesion</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  <!-- Mix Design -->
  <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-6">
    <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-purple-700">Parging Mix Design & Application</h4>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div>
        <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-sm">Standard Mix Ratio</h5>
        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
          <ul class="text-xs space-y-1">
            <li><strong>Type S Mortar:</strong> 1:3 (cement:sand)</li>
            <li><strong>Masonry Cement:</strong> 1:2.5-3</li>
            <li><strong>Plasticizer:</strong> Optional for workability</li>
            <li><strong>Fibers:</strong> Reduce cracking</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-sm">Application Tips</h5>
        <ul class="text-xs space-y-1">
          <li>• Dampen substrate first</li>
          <li>• Apply in 2 coats</li>
          <li>• Scratch first coat</li>
          <li>• Moist cure 3-7 days</li>
          <li>• Protect from freezing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6 text-xs text-slate-500 border-t pt-3">
    <p><strong>Reference:</strong> NBC 2015 Part 9, Section 9.15.6 - Parging and Finishing</p>
    <p>Proper parging is essential for effective dampproofing and waterproofing systems.</p>
  </div>
</div>